# Important Interview Points

## Key Points

- Object class is superclass of all Java classes.
- Every class automatically inherits Object class methods.
- `toString()` and `equals()` are commonly overridden.
- `hashCode()` is mainly used in collections.
- `wait()`, `notify()`, and `notifyAll()` are used in multithreading.

---

# Difference Between == and equals()

| == | equals() |
|---|---|
| Compares memory addresses | Compares content |
| Operator | Method |
| Used for reference comparison | Used for value comparison |

## Example

```java
String s1 = new String("Java");
String s2 = new String("Java");

System.out.println(s1 == s2);
System.out.println(s1.equals(s2));
```

## Output

```java
false
true
```

